# GoalifyNow Cursor Rules Index

These `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files are the **primary source of truth** for AI assistant behavior in this repository.

## Agent behavior (always-on)

- **00 - SubAgent - Disable.mdc** — Never use the Task tool or subagents
- **00 - Agents - Forbidden Actions.mdc** — Git and local dev host prohibitions
- **00 - OpenAI Agentic Workflow.mdc** — Tool-first, complete the task
- **00 - Cursor AI Prompting Rules.mdc** — How to use templates
- **00 - Agent - Execution Rules.mdc** — No early stop, verification, single-agent context
- **01 - core.mdc** — Persona, operating principles, repo layout
- **.cursorrules.mdc** — Documentation policy, comment policy, response style

## Templates (manual)

- **02 - request.mdc** — Feature / modification prompt
- **03 - refresh.mdc** — Re-diagnosis after a failed fix

## Backend (.NET)

- **04 - csharp.mdc** — C# conventions
- **00 - EFCore - core.mdc** — EF Core patterns
- **00 - Backend - Testing.mdc** — xUnit, Shouldly, integration tests
- **GoalifyNow.Api - core.mdc** — API project under `backend/`

## Frontend & mobile

- **GoalifyNow.WebApp - core.mdc** — Angular app under `apps/webapp`
- **GoalifyNow.Mobile - core.mdc** — Tauri `mobile/` wrapper

## Cross-cutting

- **00 - Security - Authentication.mdc** — Auth patterns
- **00 - Security - Best Practices.mdc** — Hardening checklist
- **00 - Integration - Backend Frontend.mdc** — Web and API integration

## E2E

- **00 - E2E Testing.mdc** — Structure and conventions
- **00 - E2E Testing - Playwright.mdc** — Playwright specifics
- **00 - E2E Testing - Best Practices.mdc** — Stability and tagging

